The paper discusses foundational features of graph query languages, which are primarily used in graph databases. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses navigational expressions, which involve recursive traversal of graphs, making it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The paper also discusses graph patterns and their semantics, which are related to graph algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely category. The paper also discusses the expressivity and complexity of graph query languages, which are related to computational complexity and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of formalization and the need for future research, which are relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
